00:36.129 --> 00:39.129
Argh!

00:39.215 --> 00:41.215
Argh!

00:41.284 --> 00:42.284
Help!

00:43.861 --> 00:47.861
Get the beast out
before it cleaves me in two!

00:53.778 --> 00:57.678
Get your bastard hands inside me
and tug the bugger free!

00:57.716 --> 00:58.716
Fetch Treves.

01:04.715 --> 01:05.715
Chloroform, now!

01:05.716 --> 01:07.015
Which nimgimmer's this, then?

01:07.016 --> 01:10.016
The one who's to cut you open,
woman.

02:15.716 --> 02:19.715
Please, sir, he's mine.
I beg you!

02:19.716 --> 02:21.716
Please do not take him from me!

02:28.716 --> 02:31.715
Morning porter found her,
at the foot of the Eastern Stair.

02:31.716 --> 02:33.715
She came to you when?

02:33.716 --> 02:36.715
A touch after eight
this night last,

02:36.716 --> 02:40.715
as I prepared my testimony for the
Linklater enquiry. She was filthy.

02:40.716 --> 02:42.715
Cursed like a stevedore.

02:42.716 --> 02:47.715
Her son delivered by Caesar
one hour later and now removed.

02:47.716 --> 02:50.715
We know not where. Or by whom.

02:50.716 --> 02:53.715
Whoever pushed her down
that stairwell, I should think.

02:53.716 --> 02:55.715
With a mother now dead, poor child,

02:55.716 --> 02:57.715
vulnerable does not quite cover it,
Inspector.

02:57.716 --> 02:58.715
No belongings?

02:58.716 --> 03:01.715
Nothing to say her name
or who might miss her now?

03:01.716 --> 03:02.715
None.

03:02.716 --> 03:05.715
Then she goes
to my American at Leman Street.

03:05.716 --> 03:08.716
One last thing you should see.

03:11.716 --> 03:13.716
Sergeant, help me turn her.

03:14.716 --> 03:16.716
It may help identify her.

03:26.716 --> 03:27.716
Oh, blimey.

